args: I've been trying not to see that!\nI've been trying not to think about it!\nAND I DON'T WANNA SEE IT NOW!
Well, heck! Notte's down there shakin' like\na leaf in a stiff breeze... Lord Seimei!\nLord Seimei! Something's real wrong here!

I am well aware, you stupid fox, so quit
shaking me! Sadly, it seems the fear in
Notte's heart was much stronger than we
initially imagined.
The spell was too effective, and now she's\nlost the will to fight. Not a great situation.
Ya gotta save her, Lord Seimei!\nYa just gotta!
Unfortunately, the spell was already\nconcluded after her fears materialized.\nShe is the only one who can stop it now.
This is a real dill of a pickle right here...\nNotte! Can ya hear me?! Don't let yerself\nget...uh...yerself down! You can do this!
N-no... This is impossible... I can't do it...
I've just been trying to avoid thinking\nabout this fear, but it's true. It's all true.
No matter how long \n{player_name} and Zethia live,\nit'll be the blink of an eye to me.

I'll watch them die. I'll watch ALL my
friends die, and then I'll be all alone.
That's my destiny for being born different
from them.
You're right. It's the truth. No matter how\nhard I try, there's no changing it.
It's true that your friends will one day\npass before you, and I can only imagine\nthe depths of grief you must be feeling.
After all, I myself was forced to face\nthe selfsame fear once.

As you know, my grandfather was the
previous Ox clan leader. Even as a small
child, I had a vague image in my mind of
the day he would leave me.
Although things actually ended up\nfalling apart earlier than that thanks to\nDoman, but let's leave that aside.

Regardless, I was able to overcome my
fears, succeed my grandfather, and break
free of my cursed connection. And now,
here I am.
It's difficult to completely erase one's fear\nof the future, but you CAN overcome it.
All you need are the fond memories of\ntimes spent with those you care about.

I have so many wonderful memories of
times spent with my grandfather—
including how we would spend every
New Year's together.
And that's why Lord Seimei's been tryin'\nso durn hard for y'all to have a rip-roarin'\nNew Year—YEOWCH!
Do you EVER shut your mouth, stupid fox?\nRegardless, Notte, memories give people\nthe courage it takes to live for their future.
So if you're ever afraid of what the future\nmight hold, go make some memories that\ncan help you overcome it.
If you just keep that frame of mind,\nthe fears you face here today should be\na simple thing to defeat.

Though if you get too caught up in your
memories, you'll turn into one of those
idiots who can't let go of the past.
Don't do that.
Use them properly to overcome your fear,\nand those memories will guide you to a\nhope that allows you to live for the future.
Hey, Seimei? Can I ask you something?
What hope did YOU find once you were\nall alone in the world?

The hope I'd one day become a great
onmyoji like my grandfather—one worthy
of being the master of both Kuzunoha
and Gozu Tenno.
As well as the hope I might pass on my\ngrandfather's teachings to them and ensure\nour memories are forever connected.
So your memories with your grandfather\nbecame your hope, huh? Thank you for\ntelling me all that.
I think I have the courage to get up now.
Isn't it obvious? I want to beat this trial\nand enjoy the rest of my New Year's.
That's how I'll make all sorts of wonderful\nmemories, and I can't let something like\nthis stop it from happening!
You say that, but it's easy to see\nthat you're still afraid!
I'll ask again: How are you still going?
Because I love the time I spend with\neveryone, and I know that time is where\nI'll find my hope.
I won't let myself be taken out by fear,\nand I won't let anyone get in the way of me\nmaking memories with the people I love.
This is...the hope I have...\nWith this...maybe someday...
Ya sure did! Hoo-eee, Notte!\nI'm happier'n a full cow at milkin' time!
Ya got past the third trial and finished the\nwhole durn task! Look at the ground!
The ground's glowing and there's a\n＂Challenge Complete＂ stamp on it!\nWooo! Yay, me! Yay, me! Yay... Huh?
Notte! Thank goodness we finally\ncaught up with you!
For real! Now let's check this square...\nAw, man! It's another Stop dealie!\n...Er, but wait. It's already done?
Notte, did you complete this alone?
Yep! Finished it just a second ago.
That couldn't have been easy, Notte.\nNice job!
Hee hee! Yeah, I just gave it my all—\nplus got little bit of help from a certain\nsomebody...
Ha! Musta been Kuzunoha, 'cause there\nain't no way he woulda... Er, right?
Hee hee! It's a secret! Pretty sure the\nperson who helped me would get all\nblushy about it if I told.
Anyway, let's hurry up and keep playing,\n'cause I'm more excited than ever now\nthat you're here!
I just know we can clear any challenge\nthat comes our way!
